Perfect 👍 I’ll now explain this Bastion Server + NAT Gateway setup in the same detailed way — exactly which tab, which option, what to click.

I’ll structure this as:

Create VPC (quick recap)

Create Bastion + Private server

Configure Security Groups correctly

SSH flow (Local → Bastion → Private)

Add NAT Gateway (for internet in private subnet)

Test everything properly

I am referencing your document here 

56cb1809-3e19-43a5-822e-be4f2b5…

✅ PART 1 — Create VPC (Same as Before)

(If already created, skip)

AWS Console → Search → VPC

Click Your VPCs

Click Create VPC

Select VPC only

Fill:

Name: Custom-VPC

IPv4 CIDR: 10.0.0.0/16

Click Create VPC

✅ PART 2 — Create Subnets
🔹 Create Public Subnet (Bastion)

Left menu → Subnets

Click Create subnet

Fill:

VPC → Custom-VPC

Subnet name → Public-Subnet

AZ → us-east-1a

CIDR → 10.0.1.0/24

Click Create subnet

🔹 Create Private Subnet (DB Server)

Again click Create subnet

Fill:

VPC → Custom-VPC

Subnet name → Private-Subnet

AZ → same AZ

CIDR → 10.0.2.0/24

Click Create subnet

✅ PART 3 — Internet Gateway (For Bastion Only)

Left menu → Internet Gateways

Click Create internet gateway

Name → Custom-IGW

Click Create

Now:

Select IGW

Click Actions

Click Attach to VPC

Select Custom-VPC

Click Attach

✅ PART 4 — Make Public Subnet Public
🔹 Create Public Route Table

Left menu → Route Tables

Click Create route table

Fill:

Name → Public-Route

VPC → Custom-VPC

Click Create

🔹 Add Internet Route

Select Public-Route

Click Routes tab

Click Edit routes

Click Add route

Fill:

Destination → 0.0.0.0/0

Target → Internet Gateway → select Custom-IGW

Click Save

🔹 Associate Public Subnet

Go to Subnet Associations

Click Edit subnet associations

Select Public-Subnet

Click Save

Now Public-Subnet is public.

Private subnet remains private.

✅ PART 5 — Security Groups (VERY IMPORTANT)
🔹 Bastion Security Group

Go to EC2

Left menu → Security Groups

Click Create security group

Fill:

Name → Bastion-SG

VPC → Custom-VPC

Inbound Rules:

SSH (22)

Source → My IP

Click Create

🔹 DB Server Security Group

Click Create security group

Fill:

Name → DB-SG

VPC → Custom-VPC

Inbound Rules:

SSH (22)

Source → Custom → Private IP of Bastion
OR

Source → Custom → 10.0.1.0/24

MySQL (3306)

Source → 10.0.1.0/24

🚨 DO NOT allow 0.0.0.0/0

Click Create

✅ PART 6 — Launch EC2 Instances
🔹 Bastion Server

EC2 → Instances → Launch instance

Fill:

Name → Bastion

AMI → Ubuntu

Instance type → t2.micro

Key pair → bastion.pem

Network settings:

VPC → Custom-VPC

Subnet → Public-Subnet

Auto-assign public IP → Enable

Security group → Bastion-SG

Click Launch

🔹 Database Server

Launch another instance

Fill:

Name → DB-Server

AMI → Ubuntu

Key pair → dbserver.pem

Network:

VPC → Custom-VPC

Subnet → Private-Subnet

Auto-assign public IP → Disable

Security group → DB-SG

Click Launch

✅ PART 7 — SSH Flow
Step 1 — Copy DB key to Bastion

From your local system:

scp -i bastion.pem dbserver.pem ubuntu@<BASTION_PUBLIC_IP>:/home/ubuntu/
Step 2 — SSH to Bastion
ssh -i bastion.pem ubuntu@<BASTION_PUBLIC_IP>
Step 3 — Change permission inside Bastion
chmod 400 dbserver.pem
Step 4 — SSH to Private DB
ssh -i dbserver.pem ubuntu@10.0.2.x

Success.

🚨 Now The Problem

Inside DB server:

sudo apt update

It FAILS.

Why?

Because private subnet has NO internet.

✅ PART 8 — Add NAT Gateway
Step 1 — Allocate Elastic IP

VPC → Elastic IPs
Click Allocate Elastic IP

Step 2 — Create NAT Gateway

Left menu → NAT Gateways

Click Create NAT Gateway

Fill:

Name → Custom-NAT

Subnet → Public-Subnet

Elastic IP → Select allocated EIP

Click Create

Wait until status = Available.

Step 3 — Create Private Route Table

VPC → Route Tables → Create

Name → Private-Route
VPC → Custom-VPC

Click Create.

Step 4 — Add NAT Route

Select Private-Route

Routes → Edit routes → Add route

Destination → 0.0.0.0/0

Target → NAT Gateway → select Custom-NAT

Save.

Step 5 — Associate Private Subnet

Subnet Associations → Edit

Select Private-Subnet

Save.

✅ Now Test

SSH into DB server.

Run:

sudo apt update

Now it works.

🔥 Final Architecture

Internet
↓
IGW
↓
Public Subnet (Bastion + NAT)
↓
Private Subnet (DB)

💡 Important Understanding

Bastion = SSH access
NAT Gateway = Internet access

They solve different problems.

