After filling above:

Scroll down and you will see:

Subnet

This is CRITICAL.

You must choose:

👉 Public-Subnet (10.0.1.0/24)

🚨 NAT Gateway MUST be created in PUBLIC SUBNET.

If you create it in private subnet → it will not work.

✅ Final Checklist Before Clicking Create

Make sure:

✔ VPC → Custom-VPC
✔ Connectivity Type → Public
✔ Subnet → Public-Subnet
✔ Elastic IP → Automatic

Then click:

👉 Create NAT Gateway

Wait until status = Available (takes 1–2 minutes).

🚨 If You Don’t See Public-Subnet

Possible reasons:

You didn’t create it properly

You are in wrong region

VPC not selected

