i cant see the subnet section as tags is the last section

Good — this is important.

You cannot see the Subnet section because you have selected:

✅ Regional – new

When you choose Regional NAT Gateway, AWS does NOT ask you for a subnet.

But for your lab (private subnet internet access), you must use:

✅ Zonal NAT Gateway

🔥 Why This Is Happening

AWS recently added Regional NAT Gateway (new feature).

But your lab design requires the traditional NAT Gateway, which:

Is created inside ONE public subnet

Requires subnet selection

Regional NAT hides the subnet section.

✅ FIX (Do This Now)

On that same screen:

Step 1:

Change:

From:

Regional – new

To:

Zonal

Click the Zonal radio button.

✅ What Will Happen Now

Once you select Zonal, a new section will appear:

👉 Subnet

Now you will be able to select:

Public-Subnet (10.0.1.0/24)

✅ After Selecting Zonal

Fill like this:

✔ Availability Mode → Zonal
✔ VPC → Custom-VPC
✔ Connectivity Type → Public
✔ Subnet → Public-Subnet
✔ Elastic IP → Automatic

Then click:

👉 Create NAT Gateway

Wait until status = Available.

🧠 Why We Use Zonal Here

Because:

NAT must be inside a public subnet

Public subnet has route to Internet Gateway

NAT uses that IGW to access internet

Regional NAT is advanced feature — not needed for this setup.

Change to Zonal now and tell me if subnet dropdown appears.